title: Highest percentage of terrestrial protected areas
description: In 2024, Seychelles had 68.1% of its total land area designated as terrestrial protected areas, one of the highest percentages in the world.

title: All newborns protected against tetanus
description: In 2023, Seychelles achieved a 100% rate of newborns protected against tetanus, ensuring complete coverage for this vital vaccination.

title: Lowest aquaculture production
description: In 2017, Seychelles had an aquaculture production of only 0.1 metric tons, one of the lowest in the world.
